text: Johana Moore (born 10 March 1978) is a Puerto Rican female volleyball player. She was part of the Puerto Rico women's national volleyball team at the 2002 Central American Caribbean Games, 2006 FIVB Women's World Championship, 2006 Central American and Caribbean Games, and 2009 Women's NORCECA Volleyball Championship.
